 					http://www.history.com/news/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/xultun_002.jpg
                    
					Archaeologist William Saturno of Boston University, coauthor of a new paper on the discovery, excavates the north wall of the Xultún structure. It features the painting of a kneeling man holding a stylus, thought to represent a scribe. (Credit: Tyrone Turner/National Geographic)
